Fitness and the Fat Guy learn all about how to get your kids in the best shape of their lives with Slow Motion exercise guru Fred Hahn. Fred's new book Strong Kids Healthy Kids is a revlutionary program for increasing your child's fitness in less than 30 minutes a week. So turn off the TV and head over to Fred's great website to learn more about his book and his great online community that supports you and your child at <a href="http://www.strongkidshealthykids.com">www.strongkidshealthykids.com</a><br/><br/>We opened the show with Los Angeles Councilwoman Jan Perry, the brains behind the ordinance that bans new fast food restaurants from opening in South Los Angeles. She says that she thinks there are too many fast food restaurants and her constituents want more sit down dining establishments and some nicer grocery stores as well. The Fat Guy, who isn't a big fan of government intervention in business matters, and Jan really didn't hit it off so things got a little heated. To learn more go to her website <a href="http://www.lacity.org/council/cd9/index.htm">here</a><br/><br/>We closed the show with Doug Splittgerber, who with Debra Corbo have written the book Your Body Your Responsibility. Doug is known as The Trainer to the Trainers, as he has worked with greats like Arthur Jones, creator of Nautilus and others. His system is scientifically sound and is really a template about how your body functions. Learning the anatomically correct way to exercise will help you get better results. To learn more please go to their website <a href="http://www.yourbodyonline.com">www.yourbodyonline.com</a><br/><br/>Remember,
you can find a tip a day at our new website <a href="http://www.wellnessminutes.com/">www.wellnessminutes.com</a> or <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewPodcast?id=275691579">on iTunes here</a>. Or our blog <a href="http://www.drfitnessblog.com/">www.drfitnessblog.com</a> <br/>







