On
tonight's
show
Dr
Fitness and the Fat Guy learn how to wear our life well with great health and wellness tips from New York Times bestselling author and TV star Marilu Henner. Marilu shared her personal story about why she got into fitness over 20 years ago and she gave her 3 best tips to live a much healthier and happier life. She might be starring on Broadway or on TV but Marilu is really passionate about health and she has created a wonderful online community that really benefits from her wisdom and passion. To learn more about her latest book Wear Your Life Well and her online community please go to her website <a href="http://www.marilu.com">www.marilu.com</a><br/><br/>We started the show off with NY Times bestselling author and former lawyer Chris Crowley. Chris' book Younger Next Year explains how you can live a healthier more active life whether you're 40, 50, 80 or even 100. To learn more about Chris' healthy living plan please check out his website <a href="http://www.youngernextyear.com">www.youngernextyear.com</a><br/><br/>We were lucky enough to get Food Editor of our favorite food magazine Jessie Price from Eating Well magazine on to talk about Eating Well's latest book Comfort foods Made Healthy. Jessie took us behind the scenes of Eating Well and shared some of her favorite recipes and foodie stories. Please go to <a href="http://www.eatingwell.com">www.eatingwell.com</a> and check out this wonderful magazine and all of their email newsletters which are filled with recipes and tips. Look for the latest Eating Well magazine on your news stands with the Pear on the cover.<br/><br/>Dr
Fitness
had lots of tips about how to manage a fun run with your kids.
Remember,
you can find a tip a day at our new website <a href="http://www.wellnessminutes.com/">www.wellnessminutes.com</a> or <a href="http://http//phobos.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewPodcast?id=275691579">on iTunes here</a>. Or our blog <a href="http://www.drfitnessblog.com/">www.drfitnessblog.com</a> <br/>







