Fitness and the Fat Guy learn Dog On It! from White Hat Brands' President Kevin Quirk. Dog On It! is a delicious tasting, fortified fruit beverage that parents can feel good about giving to their kids. Each drink is in a portion controlled 8 ounce bottle and has about 80 calories with no high fructose corn syrup. Kevin explained that his company is trying to &quot;promote health and wellness among kids. And have an impactful role in the fight against childhood obesity through community involvement and our line of fortified juice beverages.&quot; White Hat Brands partners with the American Camp Association as well as the Juvenile Diabetes Research Foundation. To learn more about Dog On It! drinks and where to get them, please go to their website <a href="http://">www.whitehatbrands.com</a> <br/><br/>Next we had on Sharon Jakubecy an experienced teacher of the Alexander Technique. This method has been proven effective in treating back pain. Sharon explained that by improving your posture with this method you can lose weight, and live a more active vibrant pain free life. For more information please go to Sharon's website <a href="http://www.alexandertechniquela.com">www.alexandertechniquela.com</a><br/><br/>We closed the show with Kymythy Schultze author of the book Natural Nutrition for Cats. After scolding the Fat Guy for mistreating his cat, Kymythy explained what foods you should avoid giving your cat and what foods you should start feeding them. To learn more about her books and her workshops please go to her website <a href="http://www.kymythy.com">www.kymythy.com</a><br/><br/>We are on social media sites like Facebook, <a href="http://www.myspace.com/drfitnessandthefatguy">MySpace</a>, <a href="http://www.friendster.com/drfitnessandthefatguy">Friendster</a>, Bebo, Self Growth, Imeem, Squidoo, <a href="http://www.xanga.com/DrFitnessandtheFatGuy">Xanga </a>and
