<p class="MsoNormal">Each issue of Her Sports + Fitness is filled with detailed training plans, lots of nutrition tips, in depth profiles of active women and tours of fun travel locations. If you're looking for fad diets, or super skinny models then this is NOT the magazine.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Kristin explained that not only does Her Sports have their own triathlon team, they also have running clubs throughout the country. You can find Her Sports at events all over. For more information about joining the running club, or get training tips or to nominate someone for an active woman profile or subscribe to the magazine please go to their website <a href="http://www.hersports.com">www.hersports.com</a><br/> </p>

We opened the show with Pilates Expert Brooke Siler. She is the author of some of the most influential pilates books out there. She wrote The Pilates Body and Your Ultimate Pilates Body Challenge.&nbsp; She is a veteran in the&nbsp; world of pilates and she has been personally trained by  one of Joseph Pilates proteges. She explained to us the difference between yoga and pilates. She also gave us some insight into how pilates gives you a great cardio workout while strengthening your entire body. Her Re:AB pilates studio in New York City has been around for over a decade reshaping the bodies of actresses, athletes and regular moms and dads. For more information about Brooke, her studio, her pilates trainer certification or her books please go to her website <a href="http://">www.reabnyc.com</a><br/><br/>Next up we had on Director Linda Burns and Andrew &quot;Drew&quot; Johnston, star of the new
documentary chronicling Drew’s rise from a cancer diagnosis to him competing in
an Ironman Triathlon in <st1:state w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Hawaii</st1:place></st1:state> called Living is Winning.



<p class="MsoNormal">This is a great story - Drew is an elite athlete. He stared out as
a competitive pro cyclist, but after a series of accidents and concussions, he was forced to put down his bike. </p>




<p class="MsoNormal">Drew quickly changed gears and found success
and a new career as a triathlete. But 2004 brought devastating news for his
family, his friends and his future. Drew was diagnosed with Chronic Myelogenous
Leukemia (CML) and his body literally broke down. </p>




<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p>But two years later, after taking an oral chemo called
Gleevac, and continuing his commitment to a healthy organic lifestyle, rigorous
targeted exercise and an extremely positive mental attitude, Drew is in molecular
remission.</p>








<p class="MsoNormal">Today, Drew competes at triathlons and Ironman events
throughout the country with remarkable results.&nbsp; Drew's life story serves as an inspiration to others, to
strive to be your best in every aspect of life and to never give up your
dreams, no matter how distant they may seem. </p>




<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;Their goal with the Living is Winning movie</o:p> is to reach audiences all over the world, engaging
them with the passion that exists in the sport of triathlons to encourage the
passion that is necessary to continue the search for a cure for cancer. Living
is Winning will entertain everyone from triathletes to couch potatoes with
action packed race footage, moving interviews, lots of humor and a great
original score. They hope to inspire every generation to eat healthy, exercise
and become socially responsible through organizations like Team in Training and
the Leukemia &amp; Lymphoma Society. Check out the trailer and buy the dvd at <a href="http://www.livingiswinning.com">www.livingiswinning.com</a></p>
