trying to get medical care and their doctor just can't figure out
what's wrong. When you're experiencing some of these stress illness
related symptoms like: pain, digestions problems, heart palpitations,
fatigue, strange sleeping or eating patterns, dizziness or blurred
vision. Typically doctors don't know what to do with these symptoms. But, in his book, Dr Clarke shares the stories of some of the
thousands of patients he has seen&nbsp; and how he was able to uncover their
problem by delving into their stress illness. He explains the 7 keys to
understanding, treating and healing their illness. Key 1 is to
understand that your symptoms can be diagnosed and treated. Key 2 is to
search for the source of your stress. Key 3 is to care for yourself.
