get the skinny
about Gourmet Healthy Eating from Dr Gourmet Dr. Tim Harlan. Dr Harlan is an Internist in New
				  	Orleans, who has had a love of food preparation since he was a teenager
				  	washing dishes in a restaurant. Along the way he learned cooking from
				  	many fine chefs, and at age twenty-two opened his own restaurant:
				  	a small country-French café. 
				  
				  <p class="hp"> Dr. Harlan originally was going to get a degree in restaurant management, but he ultimately chose to become a doctor.Working
				  	as a caterer throughout school, he continued to be involved
				  	with food and cooking but noticed a lack of knowledge in
				  	the medical field about eating healthy and eating well. Neither
				  	patients nor health care providers understood much about a healthful
				  	diet. Patients, it seemed, were usually told not what they <b>could</b> eat
				  	but, rather, what they <b>could not</b> eat. </p>
And that is where Dr Gourmet was born. He was uniquely qualified to combine the benefits of creating healthy tasty recipes for his his patients. <br/>His website has eatTHISdiet plans for his patients and anyone else who is interested. There are diets that are low cholesterol, low fat, low sodium. If you have acid reflux / GERD or are on Coumadin / Warfarin and soon if you are lactose intolerant you can find recipes just for you. There is even a section for kid friendly meals and how to safely navigate fast food drive thrus. Please check it out. Dr Gourmet is a great resource <a href="http://www.drgourmet.com">www.drgourmet.com</a> <br/><br/>We started the show with the Pasta Queen Jennette Fulda author of the upcoming book Half Assed: A Weight Loss Memoir. Jennette says she entered this world weighing 8
pounds 5 ounces and came close to leaving it at 372 pounds. After
several false starts, she started working her weight loss attempt in 2005.
She blogged about it along the way and two short years later she had officially lost 186 pounds, half her weight. She is looking to drop a few more pounds to get down to her goal weight of 160. Her story is truly inspiring - she started out barely able to go a half mile on the treadmill and today she is training for her first half marathon. Please check out her blog and cheer her on to her goal weight. And while your their you can pre-order her upcoming book. <a href="http://">www.pastaqueen.com</a><br/><br/>Then we had on one of the amazing people we met when we attended the Publicity Summit in New York...Carole Brody Fleet The Widow Who Wears Stilettos. Carole was widowed at a young age and has now devoted large part of her life trying to help other young widows get back on track and live a fuller more balanced life. She has a website and an upcoming book. Her book Widows Wear Stilettos: A Practical Guide For The Young Widow is especially timely now with the war helping to create widows as young as 17 years old. Her website which is the first of its kind to deal with women going through this difficult challenge. Check it out at <a href="http://www.widowswearstilettos.com">www.widowswearstilettos.com</a>.<br/><br/>Then we had the Fat Guy's Favorite drink from 2007 John Paul Lee founder of Tavalon Tea. Tavalon has been called the Starbucks of Tea. But we think they are better than that. Did you know that all tea comes from the tea leaf leaf but how it is processed determines whether it will be green, black or white? John-Paul knows that and so much more. This guy is so passionate about tea and how to give his customers a great tea experience. He talked at length about the health benefits tea. Did you know white tea has the least caffeine and black tea has the most. there are several Tavalon Tea Bars in New York City and I'm sure there will be many more popping up all over the country. This guy is on to something. So if you are interested in learning more about the ant-aging benefits of tea and want a truly premium tea you must go to <a href="http://www.tavalon.com">www.tavalon.com</a>. They will deliver the finest tea and tea accessories right to your door. The fat Guy says checks they are the best!<br/><br/>And we closed the show with sweet talkin Tiffany &quot;T-Love&quot; Davis from the Daily Candy. Tiffany as always shares websites and resources that you cannot find on your own. She is out there scouring the internet and the streets of Atlanta to find the next hot thing. Like Bacon Salt, two flavors that were born to go together like chocolate and peanut butter. Go to <a href="http://www.baconsalt.com">www.baconsalt.com</a> for more info. How about a site that helps you save the world a few grains of rice at a time. Go to <a href="http://">www.freerice.com</a> play a vocabulary game and for every correct answer you are donating some rice to hungry people. Tiffany also mentioned that a great way to start the new year off on the right foot is to start a gratitude journal. Every night before bed just take a moment to write down what you are grateful for. This might be a nice gesture from the stranger who held the door open for you or a kind word you child said to you. Only write about the good things that happened to you and you'll have a much better attidue the next day. For more great stuff from tiffany please sign up for the Daily Candy newsletter at <a href="http://www.dailycandy.com">www.dailycandy.com</a>.<br/><br/>Amazingly
