a&nbsp;few of Dr. Fitness' secrets...Number 1, use props and smaller plates in order to really visualize what a proper portion size looks like. For example the meat portion of your meal should be no bigger than a deck of cards. Number 2, When you are eating...concentrate on your food, bite by bite. Eating slowly and chewing deliberately will help you feel full faster. And
Number
3, listen to your body. Pay attention for cues that you are full. And when you feel full - stop eating. Also don't eat if you are feeling full to begin with. There
